hands_on_practices.solution:
1. In-plane modes (2D, linear dispersion $\omega=v_{2D}k$, g=2):  
   Density of states  
   $$D_{2D}(\omega)=\frac{gA}{2\pi}\frac{k}{d\omega/dk}
                =\frac{2A}{2\pi}\frac{(\omega/v_{2D})}{v_{2D}}
                =\frac{A}{\pi v_{2D}^2}\,\omega.$$  
   Total energy per mole ($N\to N_A$, $A=N/\sigma=N_A/\sigma$)  
   $$U_{2D}=\int_0^\infty D_{2D}(\omega)\,\frac{\hbar \omega}{e^{\hbar \omega/(k_BT)}-1}\,d\omega
           =\frac{A\hbar}{\pi v_{2D}^2}
            \int_0^\infty\frac{\omega^2}{e^{\hbar \omega/(k_BT)}-1}d\omega.$$  
   With $x=\hbar \omega/(k_BT)$ and $\int_0^\infty x^2/(e^x-1)dx=2\,\zeta(3)$,  
   $$U_{2D}
     =\frac{A\hbar}{\pi v_{2D}^2}\,
      \frac{(k_BT)^3}{\hbar^3}\,2\zeta(3)
     =\frac{2A\,\zeta(3)\,k_B^3T^3}{\pi\,\hbar^2v_{2D}^2}.$$  
   Hence  
   $$c_{V,2D}=\frac{dU_{2D}}{dT}
               =\frac{6A\,\zeta(3)\,k_B^3T^2}{\pi\,\hbar^2v_{2D}^2}
               =\frac{6N_A\,\zeta(3)\,k_B^3T^2}{\pi\,\sigma\,\hbar^2v_{2D}^2}.$$

2. Flexural mode (2D, quadratic dispersion $\omega=\alpha k^2$, g=1):  
   $$D_{flex}(\omega)
     =\frac{A}{2\pi}\frac{k}{d\omega/dk}
     =\frac{A}{2\pi}\frac{\sqrt{\omega/\alpha}}{2\alpha\sqrt{\omega/\alpha}}
     =\frac{A}{4\pi\alpha}.$$  
   Total energy per mole  
   $$U_{flex}=\int_0^\infty D_{flex}(\omega)\,\frac{\hbar \omega}{e^{\hbar \omega/(k_BT)}-1}d\omega
              =\frac{A\hbar}{4\pi\alpha}
               \int_0^\infty\frac{\omega}{e^{\hbar \omega/(k_BT)}-1}d\omega.$$  
   With $x=\hbar \omega/(k_BT)$ and $\int_0^\infty x/(e^x-1)dx=\pi^2/6$,  
   $$U_{flex}
     =\frac{A\hbar}{4\pi\alpha}\,
      \frac{(k_BT)^2}{\hbar^2}\,\frac{\pi^2}{6}
     =\frac{A\,k_B^2T^2\,\pi}{24\,\alpha\,\hbar}.$$  
   Hence  
   $$c_{V,flex}=\frac{dU_{flex}}{dT}
                =\frac{A\,k_B^2T\,\pi}{12\,\alpha\,\hbar}
                =\frac{N_A\,k_B^2T\,\pi}{12\,\sigma\,\alpha\,\hbar}.$$

3. Equate $c_{V,2D}=c_{V,flex}$ and cancel common $N_A/\sigma$:  
   $$\frac{6\,\zeta(3)\,k_B^3T^2}{\pi\,\hbar^2v_{2D}^2}
     =\frac{\pi\,k_B^2T}{12\,\alpha\,\hbar}$$  
   $$\Longrightarrow T^*
     =\frac{\pi^2\,\hbar\,v_{2D}^2}{72\,\zeta(3)\,\alpha\,k_B}.$$
